Social Development Minsiter Bathabile Dlamini and the CEO of SASSA, Thokozani Magwaza, have agreed to terminate the services of the latter.This after a consultative process led by the head of legal services, Advocate Nkosinathi Dladla, in terms of the provisions of his contract of employment.The department thanked Magwaza for the role he played as the CEO of SASSA and wished him well in his future endeavours. SAnews.gov.za